Logical operators

1. And - $$
2. OR - ||
3. NOT - !

* Logical operators work only with Boolean data types
* Logical operators will be used to combine multiple conditions

==> Table or And operator (&&)

 value1 && value2 = Result
 true   && true   = true
 true   && false  = false
 false  && true   = false
 false  && false  = false

 ==> Table for OR operator (||)

 value1 || value2 = Result
 true   || true = true
 true   || false = true
 false  || true = true
 false  || false = false

 ==> Table for NOT operator (!)

 value = Result

 !true  = false
 !false = true



